Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Peel @carrots{2}, then cut on a slight diagonal into ½-inch-thick slices. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Mix together @ground turkey{10%ounce}, @pesto{2%tbsp} (we'll use the rest later), and a large pinch of salt and pepper in a #medium bowl{}. Shape into two 4-inch-wide patties. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and cook until nicely browned on bottom, about ~{6%minutes}.

Once patties are browned on bottom, flip and cook on other side for ~{3%minutes}. Sprinkle @mozzarella cheese{2%tbsp} evenly onto each, then cover pan and continue cooking until cheese is melted and burgers are cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> TIP: If your pan doesn't have a lid, use aluminum foil to cover it.

Place @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and remaining @pesto{2%tbsp} in a #small bowl{} and stir to combine.

Zest @lemon{1} until you have 1 tsp zest. Once carrots are done roasting, place in another medium bowl along with lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon, and pepper (to taste). Toss to coat carrots.

Split @brioche buns{2} in half and place cutside down on baking sheet used for carrots. Place in oven and allow to warm through, about ~{2%minutes}. Meanwhile, slice @tomato{1} into rounds. Spread as much pesto mayo as you like on the cut side of the bun bottoms, then top each with a turkey patty, tomato rounds, and bun top. Serve with carrots on the side.